caption: Naming
tags: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/custom-transforms [[Transforms Guide]]
title: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/custom-transforms/naming
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The transform's profile-facing name comes from the tiddler's `name` field.
If `name` is absent, the title is run through the plugin's slugify rule
(lowercase, runs of non-alphanumerics → `-`, trim leading/trailing dashes).
So a tiddler titled `$:/plugins/me/json-convert-extras/foo Bar` becomes
`plugins-me-json-convert-extras-foo-bar` — definitely set `name` explicitly
unless your title is already a clean identifier.
